	(paper "A3")
	(title_block
		(title "OpenBMS")
		(date "2026-03-24")
		(rev "A")
		(comment 2 "More at openbatt.dev")
		(comment 3 "Designed by OpenBatt team")
		(comment 4 "Open Source Battery Management System")
	)
	(lib_symbols)
	(text_box "About:\n- 2-cell to 7-cell battery managment system designed to handle and protect Li-Ion and Li-Po batteries.\n\nFeatures:\n- Estimates battery state of charge (SoC), state of health (SoH) and others\n- Reads battery voltage, cells voltages and battery current\n- Reads battery temperature (NTC) and ambient (board) temperature\n- Balances battery cells\n- Provides I2C and CAN communications to the user\n- Powerdown mode consumes < 2uA\n\nProtections - there are 3 levels of protection\n- Software protections, MCU control, safelty shuting down battery charge/discharge\n- Hardware protection (TPS1200 switch) which detect battery overvoltage and overcurrent and shuts it down, independetly of MCU\n- Fuse and TVS protection - in case that software and TPS1200 switch fails, there is a fuse which burns and physically disconnects the battery.\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
